observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management submit to the Audit Team the following documents:
(a)Justification/explanation why the project was awarded to TFI without going through the accreditation process and other procedures pursuant to Sections 4.5.2 and 4.5.3 of COA Circular No. 2007-001 dated October 25, 2007;
(b) Proof of ownership by TFI of the animals included in the counterpart proposal;
(c) List and/or photographs of similar projects previously completed, if any, indicating the source of funds for implementation duly certified by TFI; and
(d) Amended MOA stating the time schedules for the releases of funds (releases of funds after the initial fund transfer must be output-based, that is, subsequent fund releases must be dependent on 100% delivery of physical status of the project corresponding to the previous funds received by the NGO) and specific period to liquidate the funds granted.
Henceforth, we recommended that Management strictly comply with the procedures in the granting and release of funds to NGOs/POs under COA Circular No. 2007-001 dated October 25, 2007, particularly on the accreditation of NGOs/POs by the BAC or creation of a committee to assess the technical and financial capacity of an NGO. Likewise, we recommended compliance with Section 2.0 of COA Circular No. 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012 relative to the documentary requirements for the release of funds.
